As 20 others have their service year extended BIRNIN KEBBI – The Kebbi State Secretariat of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) on Thursday announced the passing out of 894 corps members who have completed their one-year service in the State. According to the State NYSC Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the corps, Hadiza Idris, while 894 have successfully completed their service year and were issued discharge certificates, a total of 20 corps members had their service year extended for various offences. Idris added that 16 corps members are to repeat their service year in accordance with the laws of the corps. The passing out parade was held at Haliru Abdu Stadium and was attended by the Kebbi state governor Senator Atiku Bagudu and other top government functionaries. Earlier in his speech, Kebbi State Governor Atiku Bagudu stated that the NYSC is the best way to instil the spirit of nationalism in youths, adding that it is the reason he and his Deputy always promptly attend any NYSC programme. He said: “We always attend to them because of their importance in the promotion of national unity.”